.TH "LIGHTNING-WALLET" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-wallet \- multi-account git-backed wallet store
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning wallet
[\fIsubcommand\fR] [\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.nf
lightning wallet — multi-account git-backed wallet store.

Implements FEAT-174 + FEAT-193 (SQLite store) + FEAT-174's
git push/pull round-trip.

Subcommands:
  new <name>           initialise a new wallet repo
  use <name>           set the active wallet (writes ~/.lightning/active)
  list                 list wallets
  active               print active wallet name
  push [<remote>]      git push the wallet repo
  pull [<remote>]      git pull, then rebuild state.db
  sync [<remote>]      pull + push
  path                 print the active wallet's filesystem path
.fi
.SH USAGE
.nf
usage: lightning wallet <subcommand> [args]

subcommands:
   new <name>           initialise a new wallet repo
   use <name>           set the active wallet
   list                 list wallets
   active               print the active wallet name
   path                 print the active wallet's filesystem path
   push [<remote>]      git push the wallet repo
   pull [<remote>]      git pull + rebuild state.db
   sync [<remote>]      pull + push
   stats [--field <name>]      comprehensive JSON wallet statistics
   count                       number of wallets
   balance-lightning           spendable/receivable via lightning channels
   balance-onchain             confirmed on-chain balance
   balance-total               combined on-chain + lightning balance
   check-integrity [<wallet>]  SQLite PRAGMA integrity_check
   history-export [<wallet>]   export transaction history as JSON
   info-json [<wallet>]        wallet metadata as JSON
   address-new [<wallet>]      generate a new on-chain address
   address-list                list on-chain addresses from listaddresses
   network                     show network/chain from getinfo
   backup-create [<wallet>]    create a timestamped DB backup
   export-json [<wallet>]      export wallet meta as JSON
   ledger-add <w> <dir> <sat> [note]  add a ledger entry
   pin-set <wallet> <pin>      set a PIN (stored as SHA-256 hash)
   pin-verify <wallet> <pin>   verify a PIN against stored hash
   encrypt-check [<wallet>]    check if wallet has an encryption hash set
.fi
.SH STATS
.nf
lightning wallet stats [--field <name>]

Runs a single pass over listfunds + listinvoices (from lightning-cli)
plus SQLite counts from the active wallet DB. Fields include:
  wallet_count, transaction_count, invoice_db_count, label_count,
  note_count, meta_count, onchain_confirmed_msat, onchain_unconfirmed_msat,
  lightning_spendable_msat, lightning_receivable_msat, total_msat,
  invoice_paid_count, invoice_unpaid_count, invoice_expired_count,
  invoice_total_received_msat.

Use --field <name> to extract a single value.
.fi
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR lightning (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Part of the \fBlightning\fR educational Lightning Network frontend.
